Description: Handle of Knidian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp.
Type series: KT1648 (in Grace's unpublished Knidian Type series)
Curator's comments: Only known from Petrie's drawing in his Journal, 1884-5, p.88, 6; the Knidian stamp British Museum 1925,0119.537 has a prominent symbol, which Petrie should have noted, but the type of stamp is similar. Name, Pythokritos
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0343)
